        <cost name="Warband Rating" typeId="wb-rating" value="5"/>
      </costs>
      <modifiers>
        <modifier type="set" value="0" field="c0f3-9d0d-9753-6d02">
          <conditionGroups>
            <conditionGroup type="and">
              <conditions>
                <condition type="atLeast" value="2" field="selections" scope="roster" childId="ab2d-864e-ae49-9e0e" shared="true" childName="Champion"/>
                <condition type="atLeast" value="2" field="selections" scope="roster" childId="ead9-7109-e5b6-1cb7" shared="true" childName="Youngblood"/>
              </conditions>
            </conditionGroup>
          </conditionGroups>
        </modifier>
      </modifiers>
      <rules>
        <rule name="Loner" id="aaa3-1929-7ea0-0d6d" hidden="false">
          <description>Few people care to spend any length of time in the company of a priest of Morr - even when it is their duty to do so.


As such, a priest of Morr is used to being alone and probably prefers it that way. 


Priests of Morr do not suffer from the All Alone rules.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Funerary Rites" id="709d-c5b3-dbba-4e1d" hidden="false">
          <description>Priests of Morr are not wizards by any means, however, they do have numerous Funerary Rites, which they may perform.


As such, priests of Morr may choose a Funerary Rite listed below, using the rules for Magic on page 56 of the Mordheim hook.</description>
        </rule>
      </rules>
    </selectionEntry>
